Document: StyleBoxTexture
Path: godot/classes/class_styleboxtexture.rst
Summary: This section describes methods for managing expand and texture margins, and defines axis stretch modes for StyleBoxTexture.

Methods:
- Method: get_expand_margin(margin: Side) -> float
  Returns the expand margin for the specified side.
- Method: get_texture_margin(margin: Side) -> float
  Returns the texture margin for the specified side.
- Method: set_expand_margin(margin: Side, size: float) -> void
  Sets the expand margin for the specified side.
- Method: set_expand_margin_all(size: float) -> void
  Sets the expand margin for all sides to the same value.
- Method: set_texture_margin(margin: Side, size: float) -> void
  Sets the texture margin for the specified side.
- Method: set_texture_margin_all(size: float) -> void
  Sets the texture margin for all sides to the same value.

Enumerations:
enum AxisStretchMode:
- AXIS_STRETCH_MODE_STRETCH = 0: Stretch the stylebox's texture. This results in visible distortion unless the texture size matches the stylebox's size perfectly.
- AXIS_STRETCH_MODE_TILE = 1: Repeats the stylebox's texture to match the stylebox's size according to the nine-patch system.
- AXIS_STRETCH_MODE_TILE_FIT = 2: Repeats the stylebox's texture to match the stylebox's size according to the nine-patch system. Unlike AXIS_STRETCH_MODE_TILE, the texture may be slightly stretched to make the nine-patch texture tile seamlessly.
---CHUNK---
Document: StyleBoxTexture
Path: godot/classes/class_styleboxtexture.rst
Summary: This section details the properties of StyleBoxTexture, including texture stretching, margins, and modulation.

Properties:
- axis_stretch_horizontal (AxisStretchMode): Controls how the stylebox's texture will be stretched or tiled horizontally. Default: 0.
  Method: void set_h_axis_stretch_mode(value: AxisStretchMode)
  Method: AxisStretchMode get_h_axis_stretch_mode()
- axis_stretch_vertical (AxisStretchMode): Controls how the stylebox's texture will be stretched or tiled vertically. Default: 0.
  Method: void set_v_axis_stretch_mode(value: AxisStretchMode)
  Method: AxisStretchMode get_v_axis_stretch_mode()
- draw_center (bool): If true, the nine-patch texture's center tile will be drawn. Default: true.
  Method: void set_draw_center(value: bool)
  Method: bool is_draw_center_enabled()
- expand_margin_bottom (float): Expands the bottom margin of this style box when drawing, causing it to be drawn larger than requested. Default: 0.0.
  Method: void set_expand_margin(margin: Side, size: float)
  Method: float get_expand_margin(margin: Side)
- expand_margin_left (float): Expands the left margin of this style box when drawing, causing it to be drawn larger than requested. Default: 0.0.
  Method: void set_expand_margin(margin: Side, size: float)
  Method: float get_expand_margin(margin: Side)
- expand_margin_right (float): Expands the right margin of this style box when drawing, causing it to be drawn larger than requested. Default: 0.0.
  Method: void set_expand_margin(margin: Side, size: float)
  Method: float get_expand_margin(margin: Side)
- expand_margin_top (float): Expands the top margin of this style box when drawing, causing it to be drawn larger than requested. Default: 0.0.
  Method: void set_expand_margin(margin: Side, size: float)
  Method: float get_expand_margin(margin: Side)
- modulate_color (Color): Modulates the color of the texture when this style box is drawn. Default: Color(1, 1, 1, 1).
  Method: void set_modulate(value: Color)
  Method: Color get_modulate()
- region_rect (Rect2): The region to use from the texture. This is equivalent to first wrapping the texture in an AtlasTexture with the same region. If empty (Rect2(0, 0, 0, 0)), the whole texture is used. Default: Rect2(0, 0, 0, 0).
  Method: void set_region_rect(value: Rect2)
  Method: Rect2 get_region_rect()
- texture (Texture2D): The texture to use when drawing this style box.
  Method: void set_texture(value: Texture2D)
  Method: Texture2D get_texture()
- texture_margin_bottom (float): Increases the bottom margin of the 3x3 texture box. A higher value means more of the source texture is considered to be part of the bottom border of the 3x3 box. This is also the value used as fallback for StyleBox.content_margin_bottom if it is negative. Default: 0.0.
  Method: void set_texture_margin(margin: Side, size: float)
  Method: float get_texture_margin(margin: Side)
- texture_margin_left (float): Increases the left margin of the 3x3 texture box. A higher value means more of the source texture is considered to be part of the left border of the 3x3 box. This is also the value used as fallback for StyleBox.content_margin_left if it is negative. Default: 0.0.
  Method: void set_texture_margin(margin: Side, size: float)
  Method: float get_texture_margin(margin: Side)
- texture_margin_right (float): Increases the right margin of the 3x3 texture box. A higher value means more of the source texture is considered to be part of the right border of the 3x3 box. This is also the value used as fallback for StyleBox.content_margin_right if it is negative. Default: 0.0.
  Method: void set_texture_margin(margin: Side, size: float)
  Method: float get_texture_margin(margin: Side)
- texture_margin_top (float): Increases the top margin of the 3x3 texture box. A higher value means more of the source texture is considered to be part of the top border of the 3x3 box. This is also the value used as fallback for StyleBox.content_margin_top if it is negative. Default: 0.0.
  Method: void set_texture_margin(margin: Side, size: float)
  Method: float get_texture_margin(margin: Side)
